n the moments of crisis, Best of Times, Worst of Times features short stories by such renowned writers as Junot Diaz, George Saunders, Jhumpa Lahiri, Tobias Wolff, and many others, whose distinctive authorial voices lend urgency and a sense of heightened awareness to the modern moment. Commenting on and making sense of what is going on in America today, fractured as it is by two ongoing wars, the aftermath of 9/11, Hurricane Katrina, and the worst economic collapse since the Great Depression, these stories speak to some of the most germane issues confronting America today, from race relations, immigration, and social class to gender issues, Iraq, and imperialism. These expertly culled, emotionally powerful stories provide the perfect mirror with which to examine the real state of the union.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 29. Jul 2021) 7aLITERARY CRITICISM / General.2bisacsh1 aBender, Aimee, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aBissell, Tom, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aBukowski, Charles, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aDíaz, Junot, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aEggers, Dave, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aErdrich, Louise, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aFountain, Ben, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aFranklin, Tom, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aHempel, Amy, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aJen, Gish, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aJuly, Miranda, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aLahiri, Jhumpa, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabular